{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MwxoUT3WoesbuDhCZGdXou","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n1. CockroachDB has `crdb-cluster-public` service with ports 26257 (SQL) and 8080 (DB Console/HTTP)\n2. ingress-nginx controller is running, configured with `--ingress-class=nginx`\n3. The ingress-nginx controller configmap `ingress-nginx-controller` is empty (0 DATA)\n4. The ingress-nginx controller service is a LoadBalancer (with pending external IP in kind)\n\nI need to:\n1. **DB Console HTTPS at crdb-ui.example.com**: Create an Ingress resource with TLS. \n\nFor TLS termination, I'll need to create a secret with a certificate and key, then configure the ingress to handle HTTPS traffic and proxy it to CockroachDB's HTTP port 8080. The ingress-nginx controller will manage the TLS termination while forwarding the requests internally.\n\nFor the SQL port 26257, I need to set up TCP passthrough since it's not HTTP traffic. This requires creating a ConfigMap in the ingress-nginx namespace that maps the external port to the CockroachDB service, and ensuring the ingress-nginx controller is configured with the appropriate TCP services ConfigMap reference.\n\nFor the UI on port 8080, I'll create an Ingress resource with TLS pointing to the CockroachDB service, but first I should verify whether CockroachDB is already configured with TLS on its backend.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":413,"cache_read_input_tokens":29008,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":413},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a45e8e7c-ca4c-41ce-bfa2-78938f93f14a","uuid":"94bd6a0c-722e-4ea8-a9d3-65ec7f67497b","request_id":"req_011CcRAvjNWWccNd